The '''Namita Sunita murder incident''' (नमिता सुनिता हत्याकाण्ड) is a controversial, unsolved rape and murder of three girls that took place in 1980. Three girls, Namita Bhandari, Sunita Bhandari and Neera Parajuli, were raped and murdered in [[Pokhara]], [[Nepal]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gulfnews.com/news/world/other-world/demand-for-fresh-probe-into-nepal-triple-rape-murder-1.236080|title=Demand for fresh probe into Nepal triple rape, murder|publisher=Gulfnews.com|accessdate=20 January 2015}}</ref><ref name="badname">{{cite web|title=The Day Pokhara Got a Bad Name. |url=http://beingnrb.wordpress.com/2013/01/05/the-day-pokhara-got-a-bad-name-namita-sunita-murder/ |accessdate=October 14, 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141108170854/http://beingnrb.wordpress.com/2013/01/05/the-day-pokhara-got-a-bad-name-namita-sunita-murder/ |archivedate=November 8, 2014 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Demands for fresh probe into Nepal murder case |url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P3-1033170541.html |accessdate=October 14, 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150328145532/http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P3-1033170541.html |archivedate=March 28, 2015 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://nepalitimes.com/news.php?id=16066#.VD0Nb2eSyss|title=Lawlessness and disorder|publisher=Nepaltimes.com|accessdate=20 January 2015}}</ref> with a single witness. The witness, Churamani Adhikari, later committed suicide as per the official report and the case went unsolved.
==Background== In the summer of 1980, sisters Namita and Sunita Bhandari took a bus to [[Pokhara]] to spend their school holidays. Namita and Sunita, along with their relative Neera Parajuli from Bindhyaabasini visited the [[Seti]] river bank. There was a [[Nepalese Army|Nepal Army]] camp nearby on the east side of the Mahendra bridge. As the girls reached the river bank, a group of boys nearby started teasing them and turned hostile, then allegedly raped and murdered all three girls and disposed of their bodies in the Seti river.<ref name="badname"/>
==Aftermath== In June 2001, [[King Birendra]] and his family were massacred and [[Gyanendra]] was sworn in as the new king. The case drew suspicion when police were asked to close the case just 10 days after his ascension. The case was closed inconclusively in 2003.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.webindia123.com/news/Articles/Asia/20060507/326828.html|title=Demands for fresh probe into Nepal murder case|publisher=News.webindia123.com|accessdate=20 January 2015}}</ref>
