{{For|the Arabic language dialect|Hassānīya}}

'''Hasania''' (or '''Hassania''') are members of a Muslim tribe of [[Arab]] origin. As of 1911, they were inhabitants of the desert between [[Merowe, Sudan|Merowe]] and the [[Nile]] at the [[Cataracts of the Nile|6th Cataract]], and the left bank of the [[Blue Nile]] immediately south of [[Khartoum]].

