===Slang names for cannabis=== The slang word ''[[Marijuana (word)|marihuana]]'' was first used in the United States in the early part of the twentieth century, and was popularized to demonize and eventually ban cannabis in the 1930s. Most slang names for cannabis date to the [[Jazz Age|jazz era]]. ''Weed'' is a commonly used slang name for cannabis. New slang names, like ''trees'', came into use early in the twenty-first century.<ref name="Lexicon" /><ref name="PittNews" /><ref name="Westword">{{Cite web |url=http://www.westword.com/marijuana/dea-issues-helpful-list-of-marijuana-slang-9154114 |title=The ABCs of Marijuana Slang From the DEA |last=McKee Simmons, Kate |date=June 16, 2017 |website=[[Westword]]}}</ref>
